Review
  Review: FAIL
  The article is a high-quality, professional piece that aligns exceptionally well with the 'expert advisor' tone and 
incorporates all required differentiators. However, it is technically incomplete as it omits the final section defined 
in the editorial outline, and some ROI figures require better framing to avoid appearing as invented statistics.
  Strengths:
    + The 'Day in the Life' workflow example successfully illustrates tool interoperability in a way that feels grounded
and realistic.
    + The security section provides high-value technical depth (SOC 2, DSARs, SAML-SSO) that exceeds the quality of 
standard SEO listicles.
    + The tone is consistently professional and pragmatic, perfectly matching the 'expert advisor' persona requested in 
the brief.
